            "description": [
                "Set in the Sundarbans delta, Neti unfolds across long nights shaped by tides, storms, and slow ecological loss. Spirits, animals, and human traces coexist as the sea steadily erases land. The work views extinction as incremental rather than cyclical, marked by continuous loss. Using photography and drawing combined with digital tools, landscapes are layered, cinematic, and theatrical. Dense compositions recall dioramas and historical illustration, while quieter drawings isolate fragile moments. These shifting islands hold memory, uncertainty, and brief refuge, where light persists amid instability."
            ],
