            "description": [
                "Day Zero draws on geological and climatic evidence to examine ecological and infrastructural violence. The work imagines a future without humans, turning viewers into witnesses. Atmosphere becomes a political space where water appears as melting surface, currency, and toxic resource. It reflects on a shift from wet to dry worlds and questions faith in technological solutions. Using game-like navigation, layered sound, and stark landscapes, the work evokes an uncanny loss of control, revealing scarcity, extraction, and thirst as forms of power."
            ],
            "main_video": {
