                    "year": ""
                }
            ],
            "description": [
                "‘Beneath a steel sky’ navigates the other future - a chance with ocean colonization/sea-steading instead of space colonies. The inevitable end of our terrestrial lives with glacial melting, unstable climates and erosion, leads us to think of terra-forming very differently, more so in the absence of the sun. Nature must be brought indoors and cultivated in specific conditions in artificial climates. These chambers enveloping entire mountain and glacial ecologies, float on the ocean surface, or are secured to the ocean floor - a construction existing “outside” national sea boundaries, a micronation. This archipelago is interlinked with non-corrosive metal pipes that move the harvested water."
            ],
            "description2": [],
            "main_video": {
